library(ggplot2)
library(dplyr)
library(tidyr)
library(scales)
library(showtext)
library(sysfonts)

# 
font_add("STHeiti", regular = "/System/Library/Fonts/STHeiti Light.ttc") 

# showtext
showtext_auto()
# 107-112
yearly_data <- data.frame(
   = c("107", "108", "109", "110", "111", "112"),
   = 2018:2023,
   = c(244, 319, 312, 357, 698, 751),
   = c(565, 593, 604, 670, 834, 826),
   = c(1454, 1854, 1747, 1980, 3546, 3951),
   = c(3408, 3665, 3630, 4099, 4703, 4850)
)
# 
yearly_data <- yearly_data %>%
  mutate(
     =  + ,
     =  / ,
     =  / ,
     = ( - ) / ,
     =  + ,
     =  / ,
     =  / ,
     = ( - ) / 
  )
#  ()
ggplot(yearly_data, aes(x = , y = )) +
  geom_bar(aes(fill = ), stat = "identity", width = 0.7) +
  geom_hline(yintercept = 0, linetype = "dashed", color = "black") +
  scale_fill_gradient2(
    low = "pink", 
    mid = "white",
    high = "steelblue", 
    midpoint = 0,
    labels = percent
  ) +
  geom_text(aes(label = paste0(round(*100, 1), "%")), vjust = -0.5) +
  scale_x_continuous(breaks = 2018:2023, labels = c("107", "108", "109", "110", "111", "112")) +
  scale_y_continuous(labels = percent) +
  labs(
    title = "107-112",
    subtitle = "",
    x = "",
    y = " (-)/(+)",
    fill = ""
  ) +
  theme_minimal() +
  theme(
    plot.title = element_text(family = "Microsoft YaHei", face = "bold", size = 14),
    plot.subtitle = element_text(family = "Microsoft YaHei"),
    axis.title = element_text(family = "Microsoft YaHei"),
    axis.text = element_text(family = "Microsoft YaHei"),
    axis.text.x = element_text(angle = 0, hjust = 0.5, size = 10),
    legend.title = element_text(family = "Microsoft YaHei"),
    legend.text = element_text(family = "Microsoft YaHei"),
    legend.position = "right"
  )

map_data <- data.frame(
  ID = 1:6,
   = c("107", "108", "109", "110", "111", "112"),
  X = c(1, 3, 2, 3, 1, 2),  # X
  Y = c(3, 3, 2, 1, 1, 2),  # Y
   = yearly_data$,
   = yearly_data$,
   = yearly_data$
)

# 
ggplot(map_data, aes(x = X, y = Y)) +
  geom_tile(aes(fill = ), width = 0.9, height = 0.9) +
  geom_text(aes(label = ), family = "Microsoft YaHei", size = 5, fontface = "bold") +
  geom_text(aes(label = paste0(round(*100, 1), "%")), family = "Microsoft YaHei", size = 4, vjust = 1.5) +
  scale_fill_gradient2(
    low = "pink", 
    mid = "white",
    high = "steelblue", 
    midpoint = 0,
    labels = percent
  ) +
  labs(
    title = "",

yearly_trend <- yearly_data %>%
  select(, , , ) %>%
  pivot_longer(cols = c(, ), 
               names_to = "", 
               values_to = "")

# 
ggplot(yearly_trend, aes(x = , y = , group = , color = )) +
  geom_line(size = 1.5) +
  geom_point(size = 3) +
  scale_x_continuous(breaks = 2018:2023, labels = c("107", "108", "109", "110", "111", "112")) +
  scale_y_continuous(labels = percent, limits = c(0, 0.55)) +
  labs(title = "107-112",
       subtitle = "",
       x = "",
       y = "",
       color = "") +
  theme_minimal() +

    plot.title = element_text(family = "Microsoft YaHei", face = "bold", size = 14),
